    "language": "english",
    "persons": [],
    "text": "LIMA, May 28 (Reuters) - Peru’s central bank will raise the foreign investment limit for the country’s privately-managed pension funds to 48.5 percent in June and to 49 percent in July from the current 48 percent, the bank said in a statement on Monday.\nThe change will allow the funds to invest nearly $500 million more in financial instruments on global markets, the bank added. (Reporting By Mitra Taj; Editing by Diane Craft)\n ",
